com.avaya.cmapi.callinformation

Interface SIPHeaderListener

  • All Superinterfaces:
    java.util.EventListener
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    SIPHeaderAdapter

    public interface SIPHeaderListener
extends java.util.EventListener
    Allows applications to retrieve the proprietary customer information within an arrival SIP call on the specified device. The inbound SIP call can carry addtional user information within the "Call-Info" hearder or MIME body of the SIP INVITE message. Communication Manager will store the user information and send it to AES if the call is terminated to a monitored device. The license SA8889 or SA8891 will be required on Avaya Communication Manager to enable this feature. The call information link is one of the communication links between the Communication Manager and the Communication Manager API. The call information link must be operational in order to get the SIP customer information. The SIP customer information that can be retrieved by either:
    • subscribing the SIP header event from CallInformationServices.addSIPHeaderListener() method
    • invoking on-demand CallInformationServices.getSIPHeader() method

    If you want your application to be notified of this event, provide a class that implements this interface and provide an implementation for the following method. For those methods you do not wish to be notified of, just implement an empty body. Add your listener implementation using the CallInformationServices.addSIPHeaderListener() method.

    To stop being notified of the events, remove your listener implementation using the CallInformationServices.removeSIPHeaderListener() method.

    If multiple listeners are added, then each listener will be notified of events; the corresponding callback will be called on each listener that has been added.

    To learn more about using listeners, see Using Listeners.
